{"questionId":"22225464","questionHtml":"<p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>''</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use the quotient rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>''</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for first term in numerator, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for second term in numerator (including the minus sign). If the numerator is correct, but the denominator is incorrect or missing, award <em><strong>M1A1A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>''</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></m